(define r (/ (stat/sum z-products) (length xs)))
r
```
<!-- BUILD: runs; prints −1.0 (or very close), since y decreases as x increases -->
[VISUAL: text output, r = −1]

### Example 8.22: Zero correlation (independent variables)

```scheme
(define xs (list 1 2 3 4 5))
(define ys (list 3 1 4 2 5))

(define mean-x (stat/mean xs))
(define mean-y (stat/mean ys))
(define sd-x (stat/sd xs))
(define sd-y (stat/sd ys))

