## VII. Visualizing the Fit: Scatter + Line + Residuals

The power of least-squares becomes clear when you *see* the line threading through the scatter of points. We'll use `plot/scatter` to draw the points, `plot/function` to overlay the fitted line, and individual line segments for the residuals.

### Example 8.29: Scatter plot of the points alone

```scheme
(define xs (list 1 2 3 4 5 6))
(define ys (list 2.5 3.1 4.8 5.9 7.2 8.0))

(define points
  (map (lambda (x y) (geom/point x y)) xs ys))

(plot/render-svg
  (plot/scatter points))
```
<!-- BUILD: runs; renders a scatter plot of six points -->
[VISUAL: graphing-calculator surface, Cartesian, scatter only]

### Example 8.30: Overlay the fitted line on the scatter

```scheme
(define xs (list 1 2 3 4 5 6))
(define ys (list 2.5 3.1 4.8 5.9 7.2 8.0))

(define A
  (matrix/make
    (map (lambda (x) (list 1 x)) xs)))

(define y-vec (vec/make 2.5 3.1 4.8 5.9 7.2 8.0))

(define coeffs (linalg/least-squares A y-vec))
(define b (vec/ref coeffs 0))
(define m (vec/ref coeffs 1))

(define fit-fn (lambda (x) (+ b (* m x))))

(define points
  (map (lambda (x y) (geom/point x y)) xs ys))

(plot/render-svg
  (plot/with
    (plot/scatter points)
    (plot/function fit-fn 0 7)))
```
<!-- BUILD: runs; renders scatter + the best-fit line threading through -->
[VISUAL: graphing-calculator surface, Cartesian, scatter + line]

### Example 8.31: Draw residuals as vertical line segments

For each point, draw a vertical line from the point to the fitted line. The length of the segment is the residual.

```scheme
(define xs (list 1 2 3 4 5 6))
(define ys (list 2.5 3.1 4.8 5.9 7.2 8.0))

(define A
  (matrix/make
    (map (lambda (x) (list 1 x)) xs)))

(define y-vec (vec/make 2.5 3.1 4.8 5.9 7.2 8.0))

(define coeffs (linalg/least-squares A y-vec))
(define b (vec/ref coeffs 0))
(define m (vec/ref coeffs 1))

(define fit-fn (lambda (x) (+ b (* m x))))

(define points
  (map (lambda (x y) (geom/point x y)) xs ys))

(define residual-segments
  (map (lambda (x y)
         (geom/segment
           (geom/point x y)
           (geom/point x (fit-fn x))))
       xs ys))

(plot/render-svg
  (plot/with
    (plot/scatter points)
    (plot/function fit-fn 0 7)
    (plot/line residual-segments)))
```
<!-- BUILD: runs; renders scatter + line + vertical segments showing residuals -->
[VISUAL: graphing-calculator surface, Cartesian, with residual lines painted]

