## IX. Polynomial Regression (Quadratic Fit)

The same least-squares machinery fits polynomials. For a quadratic **y = a + bx + cx²**, the matrix **A** has three columns: **[1, x, x²]**. `linalg/least-squares` returns the three coefficients.

### Example 8.34: Fit a quadratic to data

```scheme
(define xs (list 0 1 2 3 4))
(define ys (list 1.1 2.8 6.2 11.1 17.9))

(define A
  (matrix/make
    (map (lambda (x)
           (list 1 x (* x x)))
         xs)))

(define y-vec (vec/make 1.1 2.8 6.2 11.1 17.9))

(define coeffs (linalg/least-squares A y-vec))
(define a (vec/ref coeffs 0))
(define b (vec/ref coeffs 1))
(define c (vec/ref coeffs 2))

(list 'a a 'b b 'c c)
```
